Method Detail

activateCampaign

public VindiciaReturn activateCampaign(java.lang.String srd,
                                       java.lang.Boolean forcePending)
                                throws VindiciaServiceException
This method activates an inactive or pending campaign. The method fails silently if campaign is already active. If the campaign is made active from the pending state the offer start date shall be changed to the current date.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
forcePending - If forcePending is true, activate the campaign even if it is in the Pending state. Without this, the Campaign must be in the Inactive state.
Returns:
object containing information about success, failure, etc for this call
Throws:
VindiciaServiceException

cancelCampaign

public VindiciaReturn cancelCampaign(java.lang.String srd)
                              throws VindiciaServiceException
This method cancels campaign. Once cancelled, a campaign's discounts are unobtainable. Cancel cannot be reversed, though it is possible to use cloneCampaign to clone a cancelled campaign.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
Returns:
object containing information about success, failure, etc for this call

cloneCampaign

public VindiciaReturn cloneCampaign(java.lang.String srd,
                                    java.lang.String newCampaignId,
                                    java.lang.String newCampaignSeries)
                             throws VindiciaServiceException
Creates a new campaign based on an existing campaign. It will be created in the Inactive state (regardless of the state of the campaign that is cloned).

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
newCampaignId - Intended campaign ID for the new Campaign. It must not exist already in Vindicia's database.
newCampaignSeries - Intended new coupon prefix or promotion code for the new Campaign. It must not exist already in Vindicia's database.
Returns:
object containing information about success, failure, etc for this call
Throws:
VindiciaServiceException

generateCouponCodes

public VindiciaReturn generateCouponCodes(java.lang.String srd,
                                          java.lang.Boolean invalidateAnyExistingCodes)
                                   throws VindiciaServiceException
This method generates a group of coupon codes using a separator character between the series and code (if "separator" is specified). It will optionally return the complete set of codes (using pages) if the Boolean retCodes is set to true.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
invalidateAnyExistingCodes - In the case where you want to regenerate codes for a campaign that may already have them, Vindicia will not allow you to generate new ones unless you set invalidateAnyExistingCodes to true. For a campaign with no existing codes, this is ignored.
Returns:
object containing information about success, failure, etc for this call
Throws:
VindiciaServiceException
